Digital Marketing Manager		Maker&#39;s Row		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>Maker’s Row is seeking a next-generation digital marketer to help us revolutionize Made in America for the 21st Century. The Digital Marketing Manager will help build and shape the new digital marketing strategy for Maker’s Row and the Maker’s Row Store.<br /><br />Working closely with the VP of Marketing, the successful candidate will be responsible for developing and executing creative, result-driven digital marketing campaigns as well as affiliate and influencer marketing programs.<br /><br />The ideal candidate has proven experience in formulating digital marketing strategy, executing campaigns across a wide array of channels (social, search, display, retargeting, etc.) and developing analytical insights to inform optimization. They will be confident in deploying acquisition, conversion and retention tactics as well as optimizing the performance of these tactics to achieve core KPI’s.<br /><br />The successful candidate will also have a genuine enthusiasm for design, entrepreneurship, and be able to excel in a fast-paced, high energy start-up environment.<br /><br /><strong>What You’ll Do<br /></strong><ul> <li>Help launch and grow the Maker’s Row Store by developing and implementing a results-driven e-commerce marketing strategy in partnership with the e-commerce team</li> <li>Develop and implement new customer/member acquisition, retention, and traffic-driving campaigns across paid, owned and earned digital channels</li> <li>Manage the paid digital media program including social media ads, search marketing (SEO and SEM), retargeting and display while constantly assessing, challenging, and optimizing the performance of these initiatives </li> <li>Ideate, concept and execute highly memorable digital marketing campaigns for Maker’s Row and the Maker’s Row Store in collaboration with the Digital Designer and Content Editor </li> <li>Work with the VP of Marketing to integrate digital marketing efforts with offline marketing programs and initiatives </li> <li>Identify and develop brand and media partnerships. This may included third party email campaigns, co-branded social initiatives and/or live events </li> <li>Establish and grow affiliate marketing and influencer relationship programs </li> <li>Provide strategic guidance and leadership to the Digital Marketing Associate to ensure we maintain best-in-class standards in social, email and content marketing</li> <li>Partner with the Digital Designer to ensure we develop uniquely ownable creative assets </li> <li>Analyze campaign performance data and create internal reporting to inform overall performance and ROI</li> <li>Work closely with the merchandising, analytics, creative and digital product teams to align the marketing calendar with broader business initiatives and build for future growth</li> <li>Build, deliver and allocate digital marketing budgets and forecasts on a campaign and monthly basis</li> <li>Regularly interpret KPI-based data and analytics to provide insights, recommendations and optimizations. Additionally, you will interpret data, listening insights and community signals and share these in weekly, monthly and quarterly reporting.</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Requirements<br /></strong><ul> <li>3+ years experience in media planning, digital marketing and/or digital advertising</li> <li>Broad working knowledge of digital marketing, customer segmentation methodology, engagement analysis, as well as a solid understanding of e-commerce, digital marketing and social media analytics</li> <li>Hands-on experience and direct management of online campaigns across a number of media vendors and tools (including, but not limited to, Facebook Ads, Twitter, Instagram, Pinterest, Google Ads, contextual, affiliate, and Retargeting tools)</li> <li>You must have experience in developing executing digital advertising campaigns and clearly demonstrate digital marketing campaigns and initiatives you have executed</li> <li>Proven ability to create original, unique and highly shareable marketing campaigns</li> <li>Bachelor’s in Marketing, Business or Communications or similar</li> <li>Strong communication, organizational and problem-solving skills with the ability to collaborate across teams</li> <li>Responsible self-starter, innovative thinker, analytic, detail oriented; comfortable in a results-drive business environment</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Benefits<br /></strong><ul> <li> <strong>Prime Location:</strong> We are based in Downtown Brooklyn with a wide selection of restaurants, gyms, theaters, bakeries and waterfront attractions</li> <li> <strong>Easy Commute:</strong> Our offices are within a 3 block radius of A,C,F,N,R,2,3,4, &amp; 5 trains!</li> <li> <strong>Exciting Startup Culture:</strong> Be a part of a startup company that is tackling exciting problems with simple solutions that will positively effect the world for generations to come</li> <li> <strong>Cross-Functional Teams:</strong> We are a dynamic and collaborative team that values insights from diverse backgrounds</li> <li> <strong>Excellent Health Packages:</strong> Our benefits package includes top quality health and dental plans</li> <li> <strong>Great Team Activities:</strong> Join the team in brunches, team sports, happy hours, comedy shows and group destination trips</li> <li> <strong>Stock options:</strong> We believe that great teams work as a group and win as a group</li> <li> <strong>Fitness Packages:</strong> We actively support mind and body wellness through monthly allowance for your gym, yoga, spin membership (or another of your choosing)</li> <li> <strong>Great Snacks:</strong> Weekly team lunches plus snacks all day, everyday</li> <li> <strong>Playtime:</strong> with our Director of Happiness Mr Pickles (our miniature Australian shepherd puppy</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description